com.camerontec.catalys.core.message

Class FixSendingTransformer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.FixSendingTransformer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFromMessageTransformer, ISendingTransformer

    public class FixSendingTransformer
extends Object
implements ISendingTransformer
    Transforms message into bytes suitable for sending over a normal FIX session.

    Note: this class is not thread-safe. Access to objects of this class needs to by synchronized or regulated via ThreadLocal.

      • setStrictMode

        public void setStrictMode(boolean value)
        Description copied from interface: ISendingTransformer
        Can be used to relax Catalys's strict enforcement of the FIX protocol.

        WARNING: Normally you should never call this.

        This method is included for testing purposes and, in particular, for the use of FIX certification applications. Such applications have the unusual requirement of needing to artificially generate protocol error conditions in order to test whether the FIX engine being tested handles those errors correctly.

        Sessions automatically start and run in strict mode. Use this call only if you do not want to operate in strict mode.

        While not running in strict mode, the checksum field which is normally populated by Catalys will be set only if it does not already exist in the message being sent. This allows the application to set a non standard value in this field.

        WARNING AGAIN: Don't be surprised if the protocol doesn't work as expected if you are not running in strict mode!

        Specified by:
        setStrictMode in interface ISendingTransformer
        Parameters:
        value - False if you want to relax strict FIX protocol enforcement.

      • toObject

        public Object toObject(IFIXMessage source,
                       Object target)
                throws IllegalArgumentException,
                       UnsupportedOperationException,
                       CryptoException
        Returns a BytesSegment containing the given IFIXMessage serialized as FIX bytes.

        If target is null, a new buffer is created and used to store the result.

        If the supplied BytesSegment in target is not large enough to hold the serialized bytes, it will automatically be grown by calling the BytesSegment.grow(int, boolean) method on the supplied BytesSegment.

        This method does not set BeginString, BodyLength and Checksum back into source. Caller should not assume these fields are set.

        Specified by:
        toObject in interface IFromMessageTransformer
        Parameters:
        source - FIX message to be serialized.
        target - BytesSegment to use to store serialized bytes, or null.
        Returns:
        BytesSegment containing the serialized bytes (will be 'target' if not null).
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if target is not a BytesSegment
        UnsupportedOperationException - if encryption is not supported.
        CryptoException - if crypto error
